FBIS4-60874 "drsov084_b_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Signs Edict on State Control of Oil Companies Yeltsin Signs Edict on State Control of Oil Companies LD3004135994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1327 GMT 30 Apr 94 LD3004135994 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow April 30 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree on Friday to ensure state control over the activity of emerging oil companies. The decree instructs the government to ensure that 51 per cent of shares in the to-be-established Siberian-Far Eastern and Eastern oil companies are transferred to state ownership for three years.
